<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2019a) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a) found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If two or more sources are being cited for the same ideas or information, the author&#8217;s name(s) 
should appear only once and the works are identified by the publication dates and suffix.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Studies indicate that this is indeed the case (Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a, 2019b).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are using a direct quotation, consisting of fewer than 40 words, enclose the quote using 
double quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2019a) observe that &#34;chocolate is growing in popularity with adolescents&#34; 
	(p. 34).
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study suggests that &#34;chocolate is growing in popularity with 
	adolescents&#34; (Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a, p. 34).
</blockquote>
<br>
If the quotation is greater than 40 words, the quote is displayed in a double spaced, indented 
block at 1.27cm from the left margin. Do not use double quotation marks to enclose a block quotation.
